HEADWORD: Environs
<hw>En*vi"rons</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[F.]</ety>
<def>The parts or places which surround another place, or lie in its
neighborhood; suburbs; <as>as, the <ex>environs</ex> of a city or
town</as>.</def> <rj><au>Chesterfield.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

